115 È chi, per esser suo vicin soppresso, 116 spera eccellenza, e sol per questo brama 117 ch’el sia di sua grandezza in basso messo;
118 è chi podere, grazia, onore e fama 119 teme di perder perch’ altri sormonti, 120 onde s’attrista sì che ’l contrario ama;
121 ed è chi per ingiuria par ch’aonti, 122 sì che si fa de la vendetta ghiotto, 123 e tal convien che ’l male altrui impronti.

query.result:
**English:**
115 And he who, because his neighbor is exalted, 116 hopes for excellence, and for this alone desires 117 that he be brought low from his greatness;
118 and he who fears to lose power, favor, honor, and fame 119 because others surpass him, 120 so that he is saddened and loves the opposite;
121 and he who seems to be shamed by an injury, 122 so that he becomes greedy for revenge, 123 and it is necessary for such a one to desire the misfortune of others.
**Sanskrit:**
115 Yaśca sva-sannidhau nīcīkṛtaḥ, 116 Utkarṣaṃ prārthayate, tat-kāma eva ca, 117 Sva-mahimnaḥ kṣaye tad-viṣayaḥ syāt;
118 Yaśca aiśvaryam, prasādaṃ, yaśaḥ, kīrtiṃ ca, 119 Anyasya abhyudayāt prāpnoti vināśam, 120 Ata eva duḥkhī bhavati, viparītam icchati ca;
121 Yaśca apamāna-nimittam kṣubdhātmā, 122 Pratīkāra-lobhī bhavati, 123 Tasmāt anyasya apāyaḥ abhilāṣa-yogyaḥ.
